00:50.875 --> 00:51.792
<i>♪ Bear and grin it when you're in it ♪</i>

00:51.875 --> 00:53.000
<i>♪ You can win it in a minute ♪</i>

00:53.083 --> 00:55.041
<i>♪ When you spin it, spin it, spin it ♪</i>

00:55.041 --> 00:55.917
<i>Ha-ha-ha!</i>

00:56.000 --> 00:57.083
<i>♪ Talespin it ♪</i>

00:58.041 --> 00:59.166
<i>♪ Talespin ♪</i>

01:04.792 --> 01:07.083
[birds cawing]

01:11.291 --> 01:14.542
[panting] Run! Run!

01:14.625 --> 01:16.625
I'm running! I'm running!

01:18.000 --> 01:19.583
[yelling]

01:28.125 --> 01:29.458
In! In!

01:29.542 --> 01:31.834
I'm inning! I'm inning!

01:33.542 --> 01:35.166
Fly! Fly!

01:35.250 --> 01:36.583
[Baloo] I'm trying! I'm trying!

01:37.583 --> 01:38.792
Come on, baby.

01:52.041 --> 01:53.625
[gasps]

01:55.834 --> 01:58.000
[yells]

02:01.250 --> 02:05.667
[Rebecca] 10, 11, 12, 13, 14.

02:05.750 --> 02:08.250
[groans] If only we'd gotten
a few thousand,

02:08.333 --> 02:10.125
I'd have made a fortune selling them.

02:10.208 --> 02:11.917
A few thousand?

02:12.000 --> 02:15.458
We almost got our tails tattooed
for this much, Rebecca!

02:15.542 --> 02:18.291
You and your money-making ideas!

02:18.667 --> 02:21.709
I'm an entrepreneur with
good money-making sense.

02:22.041 --> 02:26.125
[scoffs] More like nonsense.
Your schemes never work.

02:26.208 --> 02:28.500
I tried to tell you before
about the nomads,

02:28.583 --> 02:31.417
but, no, you knew better.

02:31.625 --> 02:35.709
I know business, Baloo.
Supply and demand, cause and effect.

02:35.792 --> 02:38.125
I'm tenacious and clearheaded.

02:38.208 --> 02:42.208
No, your stubborn and pigheaded
and won't admit when you're wrong.

02:42.583 --> 02:45.208
[scoffs] I would, too.
I'm just never wrong.

02:45.458 --> 02:49.709
You watch, my next idea
will make millions. I guarantee it.

02:49.792 --> 02:53.500
Next idea?
Take a look-see at our pontoonsie.

02:53.583 --> 02:56.709
We'll be lucky to get back
in one piece from this idea.

03:14.083 --> 03:17.250
Yep. Definitely an arrow.

03:17.333 --> 03:18.417
And?

03:18.500 --> 03:20.667
And you got a whole bunch of them.

03:20.750 --> 03:24.291
I know that.
But what about the pontoon?

03:26.500 --> 03:28.000
Gonna need a new one of those.

03:28.083 --> 03:31.291
We gotta get us a pontoon
or we're grounded.

03:31.667 --> 03:35.041
And there's the lady to get us one.

03:38.917 --> 03:42.583
Yo, Rebecca, I got a pontoon
to pick with you.

03:42.667 --> 03:45.750
Baloo, just the person
I wanted to see.

03:45.834 --> 03:48.166
Now, about that new pontoon.

03:48.250 --> 03:49.709
Here, buster.

03:49.792 --> 03:54.250
Feast your eyes on what I just bought:
my next great idea.

03:54.333 --> 03:55.375
[sniffs]

03:55.458 --> 03:57.542
What are they, used golf balls?

03:57.667 --> 04:01.625
They're truffles. Mushroom delicacies.

04:01.709 --> 04:06.041
-People eat them.
-Hmm... not bad.

04:06.125 --> 04:08.458
[gulp]
Could use a little salt, though.

04:08.542 --> 04:12.291
Baloo, that cost $50!

04:12.375 --> 04:16.333
Fifty bucks for a little wrinkly
thingy like that?

04:16.416 --> 04:19.541
Boy, Baloo, that's putting her money
where your mouth is.

04:19.625 --> 04:20.583
[banging]

04:20.666 --> 04:23.041
Truffles grow in the jungle.

04:23.125 --> 04:25.250
I'm gonna find 'em, bring 'em back

04:25.333 --> 04:29.417
and sell them at $50 a pop!
I'll make a fortune!

04:29.500 --> 04:34.875
You're crazy. We need a pontoon first,
so, fork over the moola!

04:34.959 --> 04:37.959
I'm sorry, Baloo,
but we're buying a pig instead.

04:38.041 --> 04:39.792
[both] A pig!

04:39.875 --> 04:41.750
[cow mooing]

04:42.709 --> 04:46.417
One needs a specially trained pig
to sniff out truffles,

04:46.500 --> 04:50.542
-one of those cute, little squealy ones.
-We need a pontoon.

04:50.625 --> 04:55.625
Besides, you don't seem like the type
that hangs around with pigs.

04:56.917 --> 04:59.417
And watch who you're insulting, Becky.

04:59.542 --> 05:01.709
Aren't they adorable?

05:01.792 --> 05:04.333
Each one
a truffle-finding juggernaut.

05:04.417 --> 05:05.333
[snorts]

05:05.458 --> 05:08.834
But... but there are more important things
we should be buying.

05:08.917 --> 05:12.458
Did I hear someone say "buying"?

05:12.542 --> 05:15.709
Yes. We're interested
in hunting truffles.

05:16.083 --> 05:19.750
Well! These miniature babirusas

05:19.834 --> 05:23.083
can smell out a truffle
from over a mile away.

05:23.166 --> 05:25.041
Imagine that.

05:25.125 --> 05:26.333
[groans]

05:26.417 --> 05:30.583
They are pedigreed and papered
from only the finest bloodlines.

05:30.667 --> 05:32.625
And how much for one?

05:32.709 --> 05:36.542
A reasonable $3,000.

05:36.625 --> 05:37.542
Oh, dear.

05:37.625 --> 05:41.583
Three-thousand smackers
for an underfed piece of bacon?

05:41.667 --> 05:44.417
Oh, no! You said the b-word!

05:44.500 --> 05:46.000
What, bacon?

05:46.792 --> 05:47.750
[pig squeals]

05:47.834 --> 05:48.875
No, no!

05:48.959 --> 05:50.291
[squealing

05:54.291 --> 05:55.458
[yells]

05:58.333 --> 06:00.792
<i>♪ Rock-a-bye baby, on the treetop ♪</i>

06:00.875 --> 06:03.166
<i>♪ When the wind blows</i>
<i>The cradle will rock ♪</i>

06:03.250 --> 06:07.291
<i>♪ When the bough breaks</i>
<i>The cradle will fall ♪</i>

06:07.375 --> 06:12.875
<i>♪ And down will come baby</i>
<i>Cradle and all ♪</i>

06:13.667 --> 06:15.041
[crash]

06:18.083 --> 06:22.375
You know, for much less money,
you can have this fine animal.

06:22.458 --> 06:25.250
[Baloo]
Get this smelly monster off me!

06:25.542 --> 06:27.125
You know what they say,

06:27.208 --> 06:29.500
"The bigger the pig,
the bigger the truffle."

06:29.583 --> 06:31.375
Only $500.

06:31.458 --> 06:37.041
Look, the truffle idea was bad enough.
Don't go buying hogzilla here.

06:37.125 --> 06:40.083
Don't badmouth my truffle idea.
It's perfectly wonderful.

06:40.166 --> 06:41.333
Four-hundred dollars.

06:41.417 --> 06:43.792
Perfectly pigheaded.
Why don't you just admit it?

06:43.875 --> 06:46.083
-Three-hundred?
-I'll show you.

06:46.166 --> 06:50.667
I have $250... and 23 cents.

06:50.750 --> 06:52.291
Sold!

06:52.375 --> 06:54.500
But we need a new pontoon.

06:54.583 --> 06:58.417
After I find all those truffles,
I'll buy you 100 pontoons.

06:58.500 --> 07:00.208
Now, isn't that a good idea?

07:00.458 --> 07:02.875
[whispers]

07:02.959 --> 07:04.166
Bacon.

07:04.250 --> 07:07.166
[squealing]

07:07.250 --> 07:11.333
Great idea, Rebecca.
Great idea.

07:12.125 --> 07:13.625
[Rebecca yelling]

07:13.709 --> 07:16.583
Gee, that sorta sounds
like Miss Cunningham.

07:16.667 --> 07:18.709
Yeah, does she have a cold?

07:18.792 --> 07:19.625
[snorting]

07:19.709 --> 07:22.500
Stop this pig!
Stop this pig! Stop this...

07:22.583 --> 07:23.542
[yells]

07:25.542 --> 07:28.500
Well, now, that was dandy.

07:28.583 --> 07:31.208
Need any help there, Becky?

07:31.291 --> 07:32.291
[coughing]

07:32.375 --> 07:34.625
No, thank you.

07:39.458 --> 07:42.333
Hey, Baloo, did you get the new pontoon?

07:42.417 --> 07:44.542
Does that answer your question?

07:44.625 --> 07:47.000
Wow, a pig!

07:47.083 --> 07:50.375
Is that what they make
pontoons out of these days?

07:51.250 --> 07:53.750
You ought to be
more careful Miss Cunningham.

07:54.041 --> 07:55.917
What if that pig hadn't stopped?

07:56.000 --> 08:00.375
That is not just a pig, Kit,
that is a means to a fortune.

08:00.834 --> 08:03.500
[laughs] Come off it, Becky.

08:03.583 --> 08:07.000
You don't even know
if this monster likes truffles,

08:07.083 --> 08:10.041
though it seems to like everything else.

08:10.125 --> 08:14.166
I'll prove this animal was
a good investment, even if it kills me!

08:17.291 --> 08:20.041
There, Mr. Pig, take a good sniff.

08:21.166 --> 08:22.291
[squealing]

08:22.375 --> 08:23.750
Down, pig, down.

08:24.291 --> 08:26.417
All right, Kit, the blindfold.

08:26.500 --> 08:29.000
Are you sure this is a good idea?

08:29.083 --> 08:32.125
I don't want any doubting Thomas's.

08:32.542 --> 08:35.792
Me? Doubt? Never.

08:35.875 --> 08:39.667
OK, boy, which hand has the truffle?

08:40.041 --> 08:41.542
See! See!

08:42.750 --> 08:45.333
[yells] Get it off! Get it off!

08:45.417 --> 08:47.542
It's making hors d'oeuvre
out of my elbow!

08:51.917 --> 08:55.667
Man, oh, man, it's all stomach.

08:55.750 --> 08:57.417
It's an eating machine.

08:57.500 --> 09:01.083
Baloo, just load my pig in the plane
and prepare for takeoff.

09:01.166 --> 09:03.083
Whoa, now, Becky,

09:03.166 --> 09:06.625
I'm not putting that creature
into my beautiful <i>Sea Duck.</i>

09:06.709 --> 09:08.458
And just why not?

09:08.542 --> 09:12.250
Because it's messy, loud,
obnoxious, ugly, and...

09:12.333 --> 09:14.542
[Baloo sniffs] Smelly.

09:14.542 --> 09:18.041
Well, so are you.
Besides, it's my plane.

09:18.125 --> 09:19.667
Who is she calling messy?

09:19.750 --> 09:23.750
And I'd like to takeoff
sometime this year, Baloo.

09:23.834 --> 09:25.792
"Sometime this year, Baloo."

09:25.875 --> 09:29.000
I'm coming. Just hold your bacon.

09:29.083 --> 09:31.083
Uh-oh.

09:31.166 --> 09:34.792
My office! My office! [screams]

09:34.875 --> 09:37.500
-Think we oughta help?
-Oh, why not?

09:38.291 --> 09:39.583
[pig squealing]

09:41.125 --> 09:42.500
[Baloo] Look at that!

09:42.583 --> 09:45.750
I could watch this all day.

09:46.000 --> 09:47.750
[Rebecca] Do something, Baloo!

09:47.834 --> 09:49.875
[yelling]

09:50.667 --> 09:52.417
[yawning]

09:52.500 --> 09:56.250
You know, kid, I feel a song coming on.

09:56.333 --> 09:59.709
This is no time to fool around,
Baloo, she's in trouble!

09:59.792 --> 10:03.125
<i>♪ A rock-a-bye hogly</i>
<i>On the treetop ♪</i>

10:03.208 --> 10:06.083
<i>♪ When the wind blows</i>
<i>The cradle will rock ♪</i>

10:06.166 --> 10:09.500
<i>♪ When the bough breaks</i>
<i>The cradle will fall ♪</i>

10:09.583 --> 10:15.542
<i>♪ And down will come piggy</i>
<i>Cradle and all ♪</i>

10:15.625 --> 10:18.667
Wow! Maybe that would work
on my English teacher.

10:19.041 --> 10:22.625
One of these days, Baloo.
One of these days...

10:22.709 --> 10:28.667
Aw, Becky, you're just jealous
'cause I have a way with animals.

10:29.750 --> 10:30.792
[pig squealing]

10:31.542 --> 10:35.166
Get that animal off!
It's eating the controls again.

10:35.250 --> 10:38.834
Come on, pig,
how about a nice life preserver?

10:39.750 --> 10:43.250
What's wrong, Baloo?
Lost your way with animals?

10:43.333 --> 10:45.041
Ooh, that's it!

10:45.125 --> 10:49.291
I've put up with your stupid
truffle snuffling idea long enough.

10:49.375 --> 10:51.625
No way am I going to let my plane

10:51.709 --> 10:55.333
be digested by
a four-legged garbage disposal.

10:55.417 --> 11:00.166
-Now either the hog goes, or I go.
-Fine, you go.

11:00.250 --> 11:01.083
[rattling]

11:03.083 --> 11:06.000
[all yelling]

11:06.083 --> 11:11.208
Mayday! Mayday!
Pontoon-less plane with pig going down!

11:13.375 --> 11:14.792
[all yelling]

11:14.875 --> 11:17.709
[Baloo] The number two engine, Kit!
The number two engine!

11:17.792 --> 11:19.959
I don't know
if we're going to make it, Baloo

11:20.083 --> 11:25.625
We'd better. I want to live long enough
to get that pig, and that Rebecca.

11:43.250 --> 11:48.041
Well, well, a perfect 360-point landing.

11:48.125 --> 11:51.625
Now I know what a sock feels like
in a washing machine.

11:52.125 --> 11:54.250
No, I think this was worse.

11:54.333 --> 11:56.000
[snorting]

11:56.083 --> 11:57.333
It's getting stuffy in here.

11:57.792 --> 12:02.291
Look at my plane.
I hope you're happy.

12:02.375 --> 12:05.542
You're the one who wanted a pig
instead of a pontoon.

12:05.625 --> 12:08.250
We ran into a little bad luck.

12:08.333 --> 12:11.250
We'll fix the plane up
with the money we make.

12:11.333 --> 12:14.667
Now, come along,
it's truffle-hunting time!

12:14.750 --> 12:17.208
She's got truffles on the brain, kid.

12:17.291 --> 12:18.375
[Rebecca gasps]

12:20.041 --> 12:21.333
What is it?

12:22.083 --> 12:26.083
[Kit]
"Absolutely no pigs past this point."

12:26.166 --> 12:27.750
Great!

12:28.750 --> 12:33.000
Too bad, Becky, but I guess we just have
to fix the <i>Duck, </i> and get out of here.

12:33.083 --> 12:35.625
No pig schemes, no pigs.

12:35.709 --> 12:39.083
Maybe we can swap it for a pontoon.

12:40.834 --> 12:42.458
Maybe you're right.

12:44.041 --> 12:46.667
No! We've come too far.

12:46.750 --> 12:48.875
[exclaims] I have an idea.

12:48.959 --> 12:51.750
Oh, I hate it when she gets
that look in her eyes.

12:52.625 --> 12:55.583
[animal chittering]

13:02.458 --> 13:06.125
Step up, step up.
Welcome to Zibaldo, my friends.

13:06.208 --> 13:07.750
And where are we going?

13:07.834 --> 13:10.875
-Um, my family and I...
-[clears throat]

13:10.959 --> 13:12.792
Just came for a picnic.

13:13.125 --> 13:17.208
Oh, a baby! I love babies.
Cootchie-cootchie-koo.

13:17.291 --> 13:19.083
-[chomps]
-Ouch!

13:26.000 --> 13:27.166
[burps]

13:27.250 --> 13:30.625
Wait a minute,
that looks like a pig to me.

13:30.709 --> 13:33.291
Takes after her mom, doesn't she?

13:33.375 --> 13:36.417
We don't allow pigs in this jungle.

13:36.667 --> 13:38.834
You're insulting my child.

13:38.917 --> 13:40.083
[snorting]

13:40.166 --> 13:43.750
-Sounds like a pig to me.
-Nope, that was just a burp.

13:43.834 --> 13:46.667
[winces]
And it smells like a pig, too.

13:46.750 --> 13:49.667
Well, it looks like a pig,
it sounds like a pig,

13:49.750 --> 13:52.500
and smells like a pig,
it can't be a pig, right?

13:52.583 --> 13:54.959
-Why not?
-'Cause pigs aren't allowed

13:55.041 --> 13:56.208
in this jungle.

13:56.291 --> 13:58.709
That's true. OK, you may go.

13:59.125 --> 14:00.792
Have a good time, folks.

14:02.083 --> 14:03.959
Wait a minute, where's my hat?

14:04.041 --> 14:07.333
That was a pig! Stop! Stop!

14:07.750 --> 14:09.834
[Rebecca] Run! Run!

14:09.959 --> 14:14.041
Wait! It's for your own good!
There are pygmies!

14:14.458 --> 14:16.542
Ah, forget it.

14:22.959 --> 14:24.625
[snorting]

14:24.709 --> 14:25.667
See?

14:25.750 --> 14:29.333
That, Kit, is the stubbornest
person I ever saw.

14:29.417 --> 14:32.542
OK, now sniff out the truffles, Mr. Pig.

14:32.625 --> 14:33.458
[snorting]

14:33.542 --> 14:35.250
See? Just like that.

14:35.333 --> 14:37.375
[snorting]

14:40.291 --> 14:42.667
Ha! He's on the scent!

14:42.750 --> 14:45.667
Soon, I'll be rolling in truffles.

14:45.959 --> 14:47.291
[yells]

14:47.375 --> 14:50.417
-Come on, Baloo.
-I'm coming.

14:50.625 --> 14:53.250
Somebody's got to save her from herself.

14:54.375 --> 14:58.291
-Onward! Onward!
-[pig snorting]

15:01.709 --> 15:04.250
[Baloo]
Hey, who turned out the lights?

15:05.792 --> 15:09.208
[Rebecca] Kit? Baloo? Where are you?

15:09.291 --> 15:11.291
[Kit]
We're down here, Miss Cunningham.

15:11.375 --> 15:12.417
Where's the pig?

15:12.500 --> 15:14.250
[Baloo] Isn't he with you?

15:15.458 --> 15:17.041
[branch snapping]

15:18.417 --> 15:19.750
[Miss Cunningham yells]

15:22.500 --> 15:26.583
Don't you think it's time you admit
that this was all a stupid idea?

15:26.667 --> 15:27.750
[snorting]

15:27.834 --> 15:29.000
Well, actually--

15:29.083 --> 15:30.458
[lion roars]

15:30.542 --> 15:33.041
That sounded like a... a lion?

15:33.125 --> 15:35.458
[roaring]

15:35.792 --> 15:37.458
A lion?

15:37.542 --> 15:41.250
You sure it wasn't the pig
pretending to be a lion?

15:42.000 --> 15:43.500
[roars]

15:43.917 --> 15:47.083
Nope, lion. Definitely lion.

15:47.166 --> 15:52.458
Nice, kitty.
How about a big, fat, juicy pig?

15:52.542 --> 15:55.709
Oh, yum! Doesn't he look good?

15:55.792 --> 15:57.667
No, Baloo, you can't.

15:57.750 --> 15:58.625
But, but...

15:58.709 --> 16:00.959
This pig's still gonna make me rich.

16:01.041 --> 16:02.875
Ever heard the phrase, dead broke?

16:02.959 --> 16:05.166
Well, you're going to be dead rich.

16:06.041 --> 16:07.959
[all yelling]

16:08.250 --> 16:10.000
<i>♪ When the wind blows ♪</i>

16:10.083 --> 16:11.375
[groans]

16:11.500 --> 16:13.000
<i>♪ When the bow breaks ♪</i>

16:13.083 --> 16:14.917
<i>♪ And down will come baby, cradle and-- ♪</i>

16:15.000 --> 16:17.166
Ohh...

16:17.375 --> 16:18.500
[groans]

16:19.959 --> 16:24.542
You dumb pig. I've had it with you.

16:26.625 --> 16:29.333
[crying]

16:30.959 --> 16:33.291
Victory! A truffle!

16:33.667 --> 16:37.333
[laughs] I knew it.
I knew this pig would find me truffles.

16:37.417 --> 16:39.625
Why, if Baloo were here, I'd tell him.

16:39.709 --> 16:42.458
My truffle! You ate my truffle!

16:42.542 --> 16:45.166
You ate my truffle!

16:45.625 --> 16:47.917
If you don't find another truffle,

16:48.000 --> 16:50.667
that's going to be
the last mouthful you'll ever--

16:50.750 --> 16:52.291
[squealing]

16:53.417 --> 16:56.125
[laughing]

16:57.000 --> 16:58.583
<i>♪ I'm in the truffles ♪</i>

16:58.667 --> 17:00.750
<i>♪ I'm in the truffles ♪</i>

17:01.250 --> 17:03.125
Come to mama.

17:03.208 --> 17:04.375
[pig snorting]

17:04.458 --> 17:08.541
Quiet! Look at the size of this one!
And ugly, too.

17:08.625 --> 17:10.709
[gasps] Pygmies!

17:10.791 --> 17:14.165
[chuckles] Truffle, anyone?

17:18.625 --> 17:22.000
[all chanting] Ooga-chaka, ooga-chaka,
ooga, ooga, ooga-chaka.

17:22.083 --> 17:24.709
Ooga-chaka, ooga-chaka,
ooga, ooga, ooga-chaka.

17:24.791 --> 17:27.333
Ooga-chaka, ooga-chaka.

17:27.375 --> 17:28.625
[Rebecca] You're pygmies, right?

17:28.709 --> 17:33.125
You like pigs, not people,
so I'm safe, huh?

17:33.208 --> 17:35.667
Where's Baloo when I need him?

17:38.917 --> 17:43.667
I thought you read in a book somewhere
that lions don't climb trees, Baloo.

17:43.750 --> 17:47.250
[Baloo] How can I help it if this lion
didn't read the same book?

17:47.333 --> 17:48.583
Whoa!

17:49.500 --> 17:54.250
Ah-ha! Hang on, partner,
I saw this once in a movie.

17:54.667 --> 17:56.458
[Tarzan yell]

17:56.542 --> 17:57.875
[Kit] Tree.

17:57.959 --> 17:59.417
[crashing]

18:00.000 --> 18:02.500
Is that what happened in the movie?

18:02.583 --> 18:05.750
Uh, yeah. Yeah, exactly.

18:05.834 --> 18:07.083
[lion roars]

18:09.500 --> 18:12.291
[all chanting] Ooga-chaka, ooga-chaka,
ooga, ooga, ooga-chaka.

18:12.375 --> 18:15.458
Ooga-chaka, ooga-chaka,
ooga, ooga, ooga-chaka.

18:19.583 --> 18:22.667
[Rebecca]
That's better, now if you'll just...

18:22.750 --> 18:24.041
[yells]

18:25.583 --> 18:27.375
[coughing]

18:27.458 --> 18:28.750
How dare you!

18:28.834 --> 18:30.542
Why you little, sawed-off...

18:31.625 --> 18:33.417
Blah!

18:33.500 --> 18:36.500
Truffle stew, and I'm in it.

18:36.583 --> 18:39.750
Well, I said I'd find truffles, didn't I?

18:39.834 --> 18:42.917
What a stupid idea. Don't rub it in.

18:43.375 --> 18:46.917
Sometimes I just get a little stubborn.

18:47.041 --> 18:50.959
I'll never let it happen again.
Ever!

18:51.041 --> 18:52.250
[yells]

18:52.333 --> 18:53.959
If there is an ever!

19:01.917 --> 19:03.917
Well, what do you think?

19:04.000 --> 19:08.458
You'll never make it as
a pygmy pinup, Baloo. You're too big.

19:08.542 --> 19:12.583
Aw, don't sweat it, little britches,
no one will notice.

19:12.792 --> 19:15.375
[all chanting] Ooga ooga-chaka
Ooga-chaka, ooga-chaka...

19:15.458 --> 19:18.041
May I have this dance?

19:20.250 --> 19:22.208
<i>♪ A doobie, doobie, doo-bah ♪</i>

19:22.291 --> 19:24.375
<i>♪ A doobie, doobie, doo-bah ♪</i>

19:24.834 --> 19:28.041
Come on, wallflowers, don't be shy.

19:28.125 --> 19:29.834
[all mumbling]

19:30.875 --> 19:33.125
That one is a big one!

19:34.375 --> 19:36.125
<i>♪ A doobie, doobie, doo-bah ♪</i>

19:36.208 --> 19:37.750
<i>♪ A doobie, doobie, doo-bah ♪</i>

19:37.834 --> 19:39.792
<i>♪ Ooga, chaka, ooh-ah ♪</i>

19:39.875 --> 19:41.625
<i>♪ Ooga, chaka, ooh-ah ♪</i>

19:46.875 --> 19:48.792
<i>♪ Ooga, chaka, ooh-ah ♪</i>

19:48.875 --> 19:50.750
<i>♪ Ooga, chaka, ooh-ah ♪</i>

19:50.834 --> 19:54.458
-Psst! Miss Cunningham.
-Kit, is that you?

19:54.542 --> 19:56.834
-And Baloo.
-Baloo?!

19:56.917 --> 20:00.041
Shh. Miss Cunningham, quiet!

20:00.125 --> 20:03.125
Right, right, quiet as a mouse.

20:05.000 --> 20:06.917
Just let me grab a few of those truffles.

20:07.000 --> 20:08.542
Miss Cunningham!

20:09.083 --> 20:11.834
I mean, at $50 a truffle,
could we still make just--

20:12.583 --> 20:13.500
[all] Ooga

20:13.583 --> 20:17.250
[chuckles] One more time?

20:17.333 --> 20:18.208
[all grumbling]

20:18.291 --> 20:22.458
Wonderful, Rebecca.
Simply wonderful.

20:22.542 --> 20:26.542
I'm sorry, it was just an idea.

20:26.875 --> 20:28.875
Wait, I have another idea.

20:28.959 --> 20:32.041
Oh, great. How will you get rich now?

20:32.125 --> 20:34.875
Selling these guys cooking utensils?

20:34.959 --> 20:38.083
No. The pig, the pig.

20:38.166 --> 20:40.583
Oh, yeah.

20:40.667 --> 20:41.917
[snorts]

20:42.000 --> 20:43.792
-One...
-Two...

20:43.875 --> 20:46.458
-Three...
-[both] Bacon!

20:46.542 --> 20:47.834
[squeals]

20:48.792 --> 20:51.250
[speaking gibberish]

20:51.625 --> 20:53.458
[all yelling]

20:56.834 --> 20:58.458
[crashing]

21:09.709 --> 21:14.083
[all yelling]

21:14.834 --> 21:16.959
[Rebecca]
We're running, we're running.

21:17.041 --> 21:19.375
Hey, you three, wait a second!

21:19.458 --> 21:21.458
Where do you think you're going?

21:24.834 --> 21:27.875
If we can just make it
to the <i>Duck, </i> we'll fly out of here.

21:30.709 --> 21:32.667
Um, Baloo.

21:32.750 --> 21:36.500
-Oh, no.
-[Baloo] I forgot, I forgot.

21:36.583 --> 21:38.166
What are we going to do now?

21:38.250 --> 21:41.083
I don't know,
but we better think of something quick.

21:43.834 --> 21:46.542
[Rebecca]
Honest, Baloo, I've learned my lesson.

21:46.625 --> 21:49.542
I was just being too stubborn
to admit I wrong.

21:49.750 --> 21:52.333
You might say you were being pigheaded.

21:52.417 --> 21:54.083
[laughing]

21:54.166 --> 21:56.750
Pigheaded, that's a good one, Baloo.

21:56.834 --> 22:00.250
[laughs] Speaking of which,
as soon as we get back

22:00.333 --> 22:02.166
I'll get a refund on the pig.

22:02.250 --> 22:03.875
That's OK by me.

22:03.959 --> 22:07.333
But it seems kind of a shame
to give the pig up now.

22:07.417 --> 22:10.417
I mean, the <i>Sea Duck's</i>
flying like a dream.

22:10.500 --> 22:12.250
[snorting]

